abstract: Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Medical Humanities have become two of the most crucial and rapidly growing fields in the current world. AI has made substantial advancements in recent years, enabling the development of algorithms and systems that can perform tasks traditionally done by humans. Medical Humanities, on the other hand, is the intersection of medical sciences, humanities, and the social sciences, and deals with the cultural, historical, philosophical, ethical, and social aspects of health, illness, and medicine. The integration of AI and Medical Humanities can offer innovative solutions to some of the pressing issues in the medical field.
